00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:24.940
Anybody recognize the
pieces on the screen?

00:08:24.940 --> 00:08:26.000
Tetris.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.060
The tetrominos of Tetris.

00:08:28.060 --> 00:08:31.140
Is there a story to Tetris?

00:08:31.140 --> 00:08:34.167
Some people say there is.

00:08:34.167 --> 00:08:35.750
And I'm talking about
this Tetris too,

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.041
there's not even color in that.

00:08:37.041 --> 00:08:39.820
You can't even tell what the
tetrominos are once they hit

00:08:39.820 --> 00:08:42.880
the pile, they're just there.

00:08:42.880 --> 00:08:44.880
And actually, that might
be that-- I don't know,

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:46.870
I think the bottom
of that bottom row

00:08:46.870 --> 00:08:49.040
is the bottom of the
bucket that's holding it.

00:08:49.040 --> 00:08:51.770
So our own MIT's
Media Lab Janet Murray

00:08:51.770 --> 00:08:55.830
would say that Tetris is the
monotony of the work day,

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:59.306
of putting things
in their places.

00:08:59.306 --> 00:09:01.680
Another professor, Jim G. over
at University of Wisconsin

00:09:01.680 --> 00:09:05.210
Madison, he says
Tetris is an escape

00:09:05.210 --> 00:09:08.830
into the very desire for order,
control, and workable solutions

00:09:08.830 --> 00:09:12.080
that we have all the time.

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:14.300
Some other less notable
but equally valid

00:09:14.300 --> 00:09:17.390
people on the internet say
it's the story of life,

00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:19.230
it's never won, it
always has an ending,

00:09:19.230 --> 00:09:22.850
and that ending is your
death or everything just

00:09:22.850 --> 00:09:26.080
piling up to the top.

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:27.830
Because it was made
in Russia, some people

00:09:27.830 --> 00:09:30.180
might say that it's a
critique of communism, maybe,

00:09:30.180 --> 00:09:32.710
or of sameness,
or of bureaucracy.

00:09:32.710 --> 00:09:34.540
Although the creator,
the Russian creator

00:09:34.540 --> 00:09:38.780
Alexey Pajitnov would say--
he does say-- that for him,

00:09:38.780 --> 00:09:40.890
it's about playing on the
edge of your abilities

00:09:40.890 --> 00:09:43.280
and about playing to
a life well lived.

00:09:43.280 --> 00:09:45.350
So the point of
all this stuff is

00:09:45.350 --> 00:09:48.150
people read patterns in
the most abstract things.

00:09:48.150 --> 00:09:49.650
So maybe you don't
need story, maybe

00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:53.700
you just give them some
abstractness and then move on.

