00:13:35.230 --> 00:13:36.860
What do we gain from story?

00:13:36.860 --> 00:13:38.780
This is where I come
in and say, this

00:13:38.780 --> 00:13:40.600
is what I think story is
going to give to your games.

00:13:40.600 --> 00:13:41.920
Even if you're making
a strategy game,

00:13:41.920 --> 00:13:43.795
it doesn't matter what
kind of game you make,

00:13:43.795 --> 00:13:45.940
you're going to get
something out of a story.

00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:48.660
We understand our lived
experiences as stories,

00:13:48.660 --> 00:13:51.300
so providing a story is going
to help a player understand

00:13:51.300 --> 00:13:52.592
what's going on in the game.

00:13:52.592 --> 00:13:54.800
If you think about what
you've ever done in the past,

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:57.170
you're always telling it to
another person as a story.

00:13:57.170 --> 00:13:59.141
The way you are able
to memorize things,

00:13:59.141 --> 00:14:01.640
often, is you're constructing
stories in your head of things

00:14:01.640 --> 00:14:02.780
that you've done.

00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:04.169
It's events with causes.

00:14:04.169 --> 00:14:06.210
You're placing together,
you're finding patterns,

00:14:06.210 --> 00:14:07.793
and you're putting
the story in there.

00:14:07.793 --> 00:14:10.380
It helps you understand
what's going on around you.

00:14:10.380 --> 00:14:12.720
A story can help you explain
the world to the player,

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:15.200
it can also encourage
the player to explore it.

00:14:15.200 --> 00:14:17.180
So if you've got something
in the game that's

00:14:17.180 --> 00:14:19.390
hidden later on, you
want them to find it,

00:14:19.390 --> 00:14:21.990
you can use story to
give them hints towards,

00:14:21.990 --> 00:14:23.450
there's this cool
thing coming up

00:14:23.450 --> 00:14:26.700
that you might
want to check out.

00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:28.640
On a parallel level
to explanation,

00:14:28.640 --> 00:14:31.600
stories provide
consistency to the world.

00:14:31.600 --> 00:14:34.920
So if you've got various things
going on within your game,

00:14:34.920 --> 00:14:37.520
the way you can kind of massage
the differences between things

00:14:37.520 --> 00:14:39.050
going on, between
the mechanics, is

00:14:39.050 --> 00:14:40.920
by covering that up
with story, or rather,

00:14:40.920 --> 00:14:42.790
embellishing and
supporting it with story

00:14:42.790 --> 00:14:45.460
rather than covering it up.

00:14:45.460 --> 00:14:48.322
So a couple quick videos.

