00:17:15.760 --> 00:17:19.440
Soul Calibur stands apart
from the other fighting games

00:17:19.440 --> 00:17:22.234
by having these complex
story lines that

00:17:22.234 --> 00:17:24.400
are actually visible to the
player within the games.

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:26.233
Street Fighter does
have complex storylines,

00:17:26.233 --> 00:17:30.940
but they're largely
fan service or outside

00:17:30.940 --> 00:17:33.200
of the game, merchandise,
books, things like that.

00:17:33.200 --> 00:17:36.850
You maybe see a little cutscene
or two at the end of the game,

00:17:36.850 --> 00:17:38.226
but not while you're playing it.

00:17:38.226 --> 00:17:40.100
And also, to really
enhance the single player

00:17:40.100 --> 00:17:41.240
experience of the game.

00:17:41.240 --> 00:17:43.490
That's actually how I know
of the Soul Calibur series,

00:17:43.490 --> 00:17:45.780
I played it single player.

00:17:45.780 --> 00:17:47.605
Because they added
